results.name: a(n) is the smallest prime whose cube divides the numerator of the Bernoulli number B(A122270(n)).
link: The Bernoulli Number Page, Table of factors of the numerators of Bernoulli numbers Bn in the range n = 2..10000, 2018.
S. S. Wagstaff, Jr, Prime factors of the absolute values of Bernoulli numerators, 2018.
example: a(1) = 5 because 5^3 divides numerator(B(A122270(1)) = numerator(B(250)), but 3^3 does not.
